[{"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion Frankfurt am Main S-2214 A - 2 - St II 23S-2214S-2214 -EStK \u00a7 9a EStG card 1 Bibliography of the relevant administrative instructions: BYOFD N\u00fcrnberg S-2214 - 3 / St 31 from 03/03 / 97EStG: 9aEStG: 9a / Application of the lump sum for income-related expenses according to \u00a7 9a sentence 1 no.2 EStG for income from renting and leasing From VZ 1996, a lump sum of DM 42 per square meter of living space can be deducted from the income from renting and leasing for buildings, insofar as they serve residential purposes if the advertising costs are determined at a flat rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "With this lump sum, all expenses are settled apart from the debt interest and the depreciation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Please note the following: 1 Area of \u200b\u200bapplication and calculation of living space The lump sum can only be deducted for buildings belonging to private assets, provided they are used for residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "In the case of buildings with several apartments, the right to choose can only be exercised uniformly, unless the apartments are owner-occupied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Since every condominium is an independent economic asset, the right to choose can be exercised for each individual apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a building that is partly used for residential purposes and partly used for commercial, business or professional purposes, the right to choose can only be exercised with regard to the residential part of the building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If a tenant of an apartment uses a domestic office, this office is to be assigned to the rooms used for living purposes for reasons of simplification (R 42 a Paragraph 4 Sentence 2 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "The flat rate of 42 DM is to be deducted per square meter of living space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "The living space is to be determined according to \u00a7\u00a7 42 and 44 of the Second Calculation Ordinance (II BV, Appendix 4 II EStH 1995)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, the calculation of living space that has been checked and approved by the building supervisory authorities can be used as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If such a current calculation - also in the assessment office - is not or no longer available, the following must be taken into account when determining the living space: According to \u00a7 44 II BV, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "the floor area of \u200b\u200brooms and room parts with a clear height of less than 2 meters and at least 1 meter winter gardens swimming pools are not part of the living space according to \u00a7 42 II BV z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "The floor space of garages, basements, attics By applying the lump sum, all ancillary costs incurred for the rental property are covered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to expenses that can be allocated to ancillary rooms which, according to II BV, cannot be taken into account, or only half of them, when determining the living space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "2 Treatment of larger maintenance expenses from previous years (\u00a7 82b EStDV) If larger maintenance expenses according to \u00a7 82b EStDV are spread over several years and the distribution period has not yet expired, the use of the income-related expenses lump sum according to \u00a7 9a sentence 1 no 2 EStG is to be used alongside the deduction of the According to \u00a7 82b EStDV, maintenance costs still to be distributed are not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If the lump sum is used in this case, the deduction of the maintenance expenses, which is attributable to the VZ of the lump sum for advertising expenses, must be waived"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "A deduction of the part of the maintenance effort that has not yet been taken into account in one sum in the previous VZ is also not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 82b (2) sentence 2 EStDV, a deduction of the part of the maintenance costs that has not yet been taken into account is only possible if the building is sold, transferred to business assets or no longer used to generate income during the distribution period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "3 Chargeable ancillary rental costs The main advertising expenses covered by the flat-rate amount also include the ancillary rental costs paid by the landlord - regularly allocated to the tenants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "for heat and water supply, sewage, garbage disposal, property tax, certain home insurance, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If the Stpfl therefore chooses the lump sum, he has the right to choose between the \"warm\" or \"gross rent\" with the option of deducting the apportionable additional costs as business expenses, or the \"cold\" or \"net rent\" without deduction of the apportionable ancillary costs no longer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "When applying the lump sum, the taxpayer must use the \"warm rent\" actually received as rental income (including all levies, possibly offset against levy reimbursements)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "For this reason, Annex V to the 1996 income tax return always provides for the entry of all levies received"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If the landlord agrees with the tenant that he - as far as possible - settles the ancillary costs with the service provider himself, no corresponding income is to be recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this, however, is that the tenant himself becomes the debtor of these passed on costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "This is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "with a decentralized heating and hot water supply through a so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Gas boiler or gas floor heating may be possible for the energy costs, since the tenant regularly concludes the contract with the gas supply company himself and may have to bear the maintenance costs of the device himself, while the costs for cold water and sewage are regularly still owed by the landlord"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If the tenant pays the ancillary costs directly to the respective creditor without being a debtor himself - e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "the property tax, whose debtor is the owner according to \u00a7 10 GrStG - or he pays amounts that the landlord is not allowed to pass on because they are not operating costs i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 27 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "V deals with Appendix 3 \"List of operating costs\" II BV - z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "In the case of condominiums, the addition to the maintenance reserve - these amounts must always be recorded as income for the landlord"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "--- Addition of OFD Nuremberg S-2214 - 3 / St 31 of 3 3 1997: Questions of doubt about the new flat rate regulation in the area of \u200b\u200bthe WK for income from renting and leasing (\u00a7 9a p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "1 No. 2 EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "JStG 1996) 1 If the legally prescribed term \"debt interest\" only applies to real debt interest,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "nor the discount or is the term to be interpreted broadly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "In the latter case, all financing costs, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Registration fees for land charges, fundraising fees, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "2 Are to be included in the rental income that can be allocated to the tenants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "What about the heating costs, if z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "the tenants obtain the heating oil themselves and settle it directly with the supplier"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "3 Are cosmetic repairs and other measures taken by the tenant to be recorded in future (without reimbursement of costs by the landlord), since a corresponding WK \u200b\u200bdeduction is to be assumed when the flat-rate fees are used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "4 In the case of mixed-use buildings, are expenses that cannot be directly allocated to be divided according to the ratio of living space or usable space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "5 Are, in addition to the deductions for wear and tear of the building, also the depreciation amounts for the acquisition costs of a heritable building right, for furnishings, gardens and assets that are listed under Section 9 Paragraph 1 No. 7 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Section 6 (2) of the Income Tax Act (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Tools)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "6 Should maintenance expenses be based on the implementation of the measures or the outflow of payments, if a change from or to a lump sum has been made in the meantime"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "7 Are larger maintenance expenses distributed according to Section 82b EStDV still deductible if a change to a flat rate is made within the distribution period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If not, the remaining amount can be deducted in full in the last year before the lump sum"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "8 What about prepayments?"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "9 In the event of a binding effect, the (free) individual legal successor / universal successor is bound to the binding for 5 years after the option to provide actual evidence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "10 Does the binding effect also apply after a MWG has been divided into ETW and subsequent sublet by the previous landlord"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "11 If the prerequisites for the flat-rate payment are met only on a pro-rata basis, the 42 DM flat rate must be divided accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Questions of doubt about the new flat-rate regulation (\u00a7 9a p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "1 No. 2 EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "JStG 1996) Answers to this catalog of questions: Re 1: The term is to be interpreted narrowly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Debt interest, ground rent and amounts for a discount (Damnum) are recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "(Note: probably not tenable) Re 2: Apportionable ancillary costs are to be recorded in the rental income; this does not apply if the tenant himself becomes the debtor of the ancillary costs, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a rented family house, he provides the heating oil himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "With rented ETW will already be legally not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "To 3: Theoretically yes, in practice hardly relevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "to 4: According to the usable area ratio to 5: Yes 6: The flow of payments is to be considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "If the repair is carried out in 1995, but only paid for in 1996, the amount for the repair is also settled in favor of the flat rate (otherwise earlier in Section 21a area!) Re 7: If within the distribution period (Section 82b EStDV) there is a change to the flat rate , the partial amount not yet taken into account is settled with the flat rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "A deduction of the remaining amount in the last year before the lump sum is not possible, as the rented apartment continues to generate income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Re 8: Provided that there is no abusive legal structure, a deduction is possible in the year of payment, if there is no lump sum in this year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "To 9: As far as I know, not yet decided; there is probably no binding for the individual legal successor free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "to 10: not yet decided; the binding effect should probably continue to exist in relation to the apartment even after the division into ETWs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "Re 11: If the lump sum is only to be carried out for part of the year because the requirements are only met, the DM 42 amount is to be twelfth accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138217.xml"}, "text": "--- Income tax / wage tax / church tax Hesse-Bavaria"}]